Rating: 3
As with most recipes, it's all about your personal touch. I don't think I've ever followed any recipe to the "t" but with just a quick few little tweaks, this one turns out amazing. I usually add some barbecued chicken breasts (marinaded in a citrus marinade)to make this a one dish meal. I have had rave reviews and this is my go-to dish for when I have casual company. Usually all it takes is a bit more salt or lemon juice and some more goat cheese and it's got tons of flavour. Don't dismiss this recipe because of some bad reviews. It's got a lot of potential, it's a great base recipe and is great for anybody who knows how to fix up a dish. Btw, dried tarragon has way more flavour than fresh and I can never find fresh in our local grocery stores anyway.

