Rating: 3
I sauteed the asparagus in some olive oil, adding garlic at the end. I cooled this mixture off a bit before adding the cooked pasta, lemon peel, tarragon and goat cheese, tossing it all together with some of the pasta water and adding S&P. I also topped it off with parmesan. Quite tasty!

Rating: 2
The fact that this recipe has gotten high ratings largely has to do with all of the people who have added to it and bettered it, and reviewed their own superior version of the dish. DEFINITELY roast the asparagus, it carries the dish much further than if you just boil it, and it also maintains greater health benefits if all of the nutrients in the asparagus don't get thrown out in the unused pasta water. I doubled the amount of asparagus and still felt like there was enough cheese to make a filling and heavy sauce. I definitely wish I had read the reviews and thought to pick up sundried tomatoes. Without it, this dish lacks any roundness of flavor. With the appropriate improvements, I will make again.

